
arr = [9, 7, 5, 3], k = 6
output true
arr = 4 4 4 and k = 4 output false

logic:
take the remainder balance and put its count in map
in count ,
  if its half value occurs twice or 2n times then it can pair
  if 0 remainder then it also twice or 2n time then it can pair
  if any other number then need to  (k-num) other num should exist then it can pair
  like 1 and 5 can form 6 
    Remainders:   
        9 % 6 = 3
        7 % 6 = 1
        5 % 6 = 5
        3 % 6 = 3
  Pairs:
      1 ↔ 5
      3 ↔ 3

✔ Valid → Output = true


Case	      Rule
rem == 0	  Count must be even
rem == k/2	Count must be even (only if k even)
others	    freq[r] == freq[k-r]


class Solution {
    public boolean canPair(List<Integer> arr, int k) {
        // code here.
        if(arr.size() %2 !=0){
            return false;
        }
        Map<Integer, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
        for(Integer a: arr){
            
            int rem = ((a%k)+k)%k;
            map.put(rem,map.getOrDefault(rem,0)+1);
            
        }
       for(int rem : map.keySet()){
           
           if(rem==0 || 2* rem == k){
               if(map.get(rem)%2 !=0) return false;
           }
           else {
               if(map.get(rem) != map.getOrDefault(k-rem,0)) return false;
           }
       }
       return true;
    }
}
